## 9. Validation and Guardrails

The validator (`pipeline/validator.py`) must enforce all V3 schema guardrails:

- **17.1** â€” `grammar_focus_key` must belong to the declared `grammar_role_key`.
- **17.2** â€” Do not classify Expression of Ideas under `grammar_role_key` unless genuinely grammar-adjacent.
- **17.3** â€” `secondary_grammar_focus_keys` must be populated when multiple rules apply.
- **17.4** â€” Option-level error keys must be grammar-specific (e.g., `semicolon_use`, not `punctuation_error`).
- **17.5** â€” No-Change tracking is mandatory when original text is an option.
- **17.6** â€” Passage-level tense/register metadata for all verb-form questions.
- **17.7** â€” `syntactic_trap_intensity` populated for generation profiles.
- **17.8** â€” `disambiguation_rule_applied` explicit when conflicts are resolved.
- **17.9** â€” Amendment proposals include parent role and evidence.
- **17.10** â€” Frequency data guides generation.
- **17.11** â€” Option text format consistency.
- **17.12** â€” Difficulty calibration rubric applied.
- **17.13** â€” Evidence span selection rules.
- **17.14** â€” Explanation content requirements.
- **29** â€” Final validation: distractor_distance, student_failure_mode_key, distractor_competition_score >= 0.75, plausible_wrong_count >= 2, answer_separation_strength, passage_architecture_key, official_similarity_score, structural_similarity_score, empirical_difficulty_estimate, provenance.

Any validation failure sets the job status to `draft` and writes the error array to `validation_errors_json`.

## 10. Recall and Generation Workflows

### 10.1 Recall for Official Items

Use cases:
- Build practice modules that mirror official difficulty distributions.
- Retrieve all `official` items with `grammar_focus_key = subject_verb_agreement` and `difficulty_overall = medium`.
- Compare generated items against the official corpus for similarity scoring.

### 10.2 Recall for Unofficial Items (Generation Seeds)

Use cases:
- Retrieve a set of unofficial items with a specific `grammar_focus_key` + `syntactic_trap_key` pair to serve as in-context examples for LLM generation.
- Use `generation_profile` fields to build a new generation request.
- Anti-clone protection: before generating a new item, query the corpus for `structural_similarity_score > 0.75` against the proposed passage template. If found, regenerate.

### 10.3 Generation Request Format

The `GET /generation/recall` endpoint feeds into the generation pipeline by returning items formatted as:

```json
{
  "recall_items": [
    {
      "question_id": "...",
      "source_classification": "unofficial",
      "classification": { ... },
      "options": [ ... ],
      "generation_profile": { ... }
    }
  ]
}
```

This output can be passed directly to the generation agent as few-shot examples or as a template base.

## 11. Security and Compliance

- Official College Board material must not be exposed publicly. The `official` archive directory should be outside the web root or protected by authentication.
- All DB connections use the Supabase session pooler (port 5432) with TLS.
- LLM API keys are read from `.env` and never logged.
- Uploaded files are validated by MIME type and size (max `MAX_FILE_UPLOAD_MB`, default 20).

## 12. Configuration

Add to `.env`:

```bash
# Official archive settings
ARCHIVE_ENABLED=true
ARCHIVE_FORMAT=json          # json | yaml
ARCHIVE_BASE_PATH=./archive/official

# Image storage settings
IMAGE_STORAGE_ENABLED=true
IMAGE_STORAGE_PATH=./archive/images
IMAGE_STORAGE_MAX_MB=50

# Generation recall settings
GENERATION_RECALL_LIMIT=10
GENERATION_SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD=0.75

# Ground truth verification
GROUND_TRUTH_AUTO_VERIFY=false   # If true, official items with known exam keys are auto-verified
```

## 13. Success Metrics

| Metric | Target |
|---|---|
| Pass 1 extraction accuracy (official items) | â‰¥ 95% correct answer label recovery |
| Pass 2 taxonomy accuracy (human-reviewed sample) | â‰¥ 90% primary `grammar_focus_key` agreement with expert annotator |
| Archive write success rate | 100% (failures block approval) |
| Validation error rate (unofficial items) | < 10% failing final V3 validation |
| Generation recall latency | < 200 ms for recall queries |
| End-to-end ingestion latency (single item, text) | < 15 s |
| End-to-end ingestion latency (PDF, multi-item) | < 60 s per 10 questions |

## 14. Future Work (Out of Scope for V1)

- Bulk ZIP upload with automatic file-type detection.
- Real-time webhook notifications on job status changes.
- Diff-based re-ingestion: compare a new upload against existing archives and only stage changed items.
- Automated similarity scoring against the official corpus during Pass 2.
- Multi-language support (Spanish-language SAT materials).

